reviews_data.review_text:
This coffee shop is such a hidden gem, people working there are lovely and so is their coffee and pastries. I enjoy trying all their new monthly flavors and its a great place to work/study.
I do wish they sold more savory options like sandwiches or wraps (but I believe its something planned for the future).
The only other thing is if you plan on working in the evening, check their calendar because they do have events and it can get very loud and I had to leave early due to noise and lack of space on few occasions.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Thank you so much Vicki! We do have a lot of events, that is true. Usually, Thursday, and Saturdays, and trivia Fridays happens outside now that it's warm again (if you're reading this in January of 2026 just know I'm writing it in Spring.)

We are working on our food trailer as I type this. Honestly, I'm typing this to avoid that work. No, I'm kidding but we are hoping to have savory food, cooked right here, within the coming weeks. And as for wraps and sandwiches I literally just bought some so we are adding "grab and go" (or "grab and sit and hang out and work or read") options as of this afternoon. We're excited about that. 

Best practice is to check our instagram: @foresttrailhouse to see if we have anything going on that evening or what our specials are and just to keep up to date. Thanks so much for this lovely review. We'll see you at the shop soon!

reviews_data.review_text: I wanna like this place everytime I go, but unfortunately leave disappointed. Their food is very mediocre, and the coffee is too. Their lattes never taste like what they say they are, and usually taste like they have no syrup at all. I think their aesthetic is perfect, but seems like that’s what their main focus is on, instead of good drinks & good food.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Sorry you feel this way Austin. We are always happy to add more syrup if that's what you'd like. I will defend that our drinks and food take up 90% of our bandwidth and the aesthetic is a distant third. Our espresso was selected over weeks of trail and error, it's a single origin from the Huehuetenaga region Guatemala. We do feel like the syrup should be the cherry on top of the sundae and not the sundae itself. We want you to taste the espresso and milk more than the syrup, otherwise, it becomes too sweet for us but that's just us and everyone has their own desires and ultimately we're there to please so just ask for extra syrup and we'll gladly give that to you. Our house blend for our is also a Guatemalan blend that we chose because most people like a medium dark blend. But if you really want a nice light blend you should try our pour over! It's amazing. We make all of our food in house with trained bakers. I don't know what you ordered but I'm sorry it wasn't to your liking. We know we can't win 'em all but as a small business it always hurts to get reviews like this. We take it personally and try to learn from it.

reviews_data.review_text: Best coffee and frappe
reviews_data.owner_answer: Short, sweet, 5 stars. We love it, thanks!!!

reviews_data.review_text: This is my favorite coffee spot in all of Charlotte! I’m here every day, enjoying one of the monthly rotating pastries and an expertly made latte. FTH has literally been a lifeline since moving to Mint Hill. I’ve met so many amazing friends here and it’s because they foster a lovely and welcoming environment that attracts all the best people! Tip your baristas well and treat them right or I will come for you ;)
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks Minna!!! We love seeing you here and as not one of the baristas/bartenders I agree, tip them well! They're working their butts off and doing an amazing job here creating a wonderful space in Mint Hill. We're very proud of this staff!

reviews_data.review_text:
This used to be our favorite coffe place because they have a wall of pictures of dogs in the shop and we found them to be very dog friendly to well behaved dogs such as ours. This put Forest Trail above other local coffee shops especially in the winter.
Today we were informed their policy has changed and we were asked to leave with our pup. There was no other customers in the store but we respected their decision and left. For us Forest Hill has lost the one attraction that set them apart from the other coffee shops so it's a matter of if their coffee is good enough to sit outside in the cold. You can probably get the same combination of syrups at McDonalds, Starbucks or Brakemans. Forest Trail should probably take down all the pictures of cute dogs in their shop.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Sorry about that Jon, it’s not our favorite rule either. You can go to ncleg.gov and see who you can write about changing it but our hands are tied. The pics will stay though, sorry. We love our outdoor pups. Also, we certainly aim to be much better than those other places and we’ll continue to push our drinks to new and better places. Anyway, sorry you were upset today. It’s been our policy since day one because it’s the law. So is it a policy? IDK, honestly, it’s just the law.

Anyway, glad you enjoyed your stop with us!

reviews_data.review_text: Saw the reviews and went out of our way to bring our family here. Spent $40, and threw our drinks out on the way out. Sticky bun and cookie was good! The service was less than kind. Worst coffee we’ve ever had. The outdoor area was AWESOME for the kids, but the bathroom reeked of urine. Won’t be back.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Piper, I really am truly so sorry you had a bad experience. We strive to be better than this and I take it very personally whenever a customer has a bad experience. I understand why you won't be coming back.

For people who aren't Piper who are reading this, the way to handle this is to come to us and say you aren't happy. She ordered two fresh squeezed lemonades, which we can easily adjust to your liking, making them sweeter or more tart, however you like it. We squeeze them fresh so we can definitely help you with that! She also ordered our cold brew with a cold foam and a latte - again, these are all adjustable and if somethings wrong, please come to us. We will fix it for you.

If you're at a small business and the bathroom is dirty believe me, we're more embarrassed than you are. But there are also customers who do not care and make a mess. Please tell us. Please. Sometimes we'll got hours without being able to get into the bathrooms because we're so busy, but if you tell us, or other small businesses, we'll get in there and fix the problem. 

Small businesses rely on your input because we cannot be everywhere at all times. So tell us in the moment if you can. That way we can help. If you wait and do it on the internet, it's impossible for it to fix it for YOU.

reviews_data.review_text: I had high hopes for Forest Trail when they took over, but man am I disappointed. We just want high quality coffee in Mint Hill but they are trying to do too much rather than focusing on their main product - COFFEE! I really want to support local businesses but I would rather drive 20 minutes to another coffee shop than go to Forest Trail.
reviews_data.owner_answer: We're sorry that you don't enjoy our coffee, we understand that all tastes are different and we strive to make our customers happy. I understand that you believe we don't focus on our coffee but just for the record, you had a pumpkin spiced cold brew with oat milk vanilla cold foam. We steep that cold brew for 19 hours, we honed that pumpkin spice recipe over several days until finalizing it, an that takes us several hours to make, and the cold foam we make on the spot fresh, not from a premixed bag. After you didn't like that we happily made you a pumpkin spiced latte to replace that. Now, I'm not sure what you did not like about that but we've tasted at least 10 different espresso blends to come up with a solid medium-dark roast that will stand up to the syrups and milk that everyone adds. We want the espresso to still shine, and we think that it does. Clearly you disagree but such is life. If you do decide to try us again, you should try the actual coffee. It's great!

We also have oat milk, unsweetened Almond milk, whole milk, and skim milk in case you decide to give us another try, which we hope you do!

reviews_data.review_text: We continued our quest of trying out the local coffee shops in the greater Charlotte area and ended up here.  We ordered food, coffee, and tea.  The coffee was a light/medium roast and was quite good but not our personal favorite.  The tea was excellent.  We ordered the quiche and a stinger.  The quiche was amazing but the stinger was super dry, did not contain much meat, and was difficult to eat.  We would not get the stinger again but we would eat the quiche all day long.  The location is great and there is plenty of parking out back.  The atmosphere here was really great.  We will definitely be back if only for the quiche and to try a different type of coffee.  Nice place to chill out if you are in the Mint Hill area!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Oh man, that's a bummer about the stinger! We love our stingers and it's a bummer that we missed on that one. We make everything in house and take a lot of pride in our work, we're really sorry we didn't nail it for you. Next time you should try our pour over or ask for one of our roasts in a french press, I love Cairn coffee and that's why we work with them. We've found that most of our customers love a slightly darker roast but we have lighter roasts available by the cup as well. It'll just take us a few extra minutes. Anyway, we appreciate you giving us a try! Good luck in your continued quest.

reviews_data.review_text: Okay so....today was my first time trying this coffee shop. My husband and I were out running errands and I needed a pick me up so instead trying to find a Starbucks we wanted to try local instead, which is what we prefer. Upon entering, the atmosphere is very chill and quaint, but the service was extremely lacking. When we got to the counter we were met with a rude, blank stare just waiting for our order with no hello or welcome, and then a "what are you having". I told the girl it was our first time there and we didn't see the coffee menu (to explain our delay in ordering) and she just stood there with no reply, no beckoning to where the menu was, nor a recommendation. We eventually looked around and found the menu and ordered 2 Americanos (we would've ordered more with suggestion or even friendliness but decided against it). After getting our EXTREMELY HOT coffees, we tried adding sugar to them but it melted the straws and couldn't stir. After getting into the car, the coffees were too hot to drink and started to warp the lids and coffee cups. Now I'm sitting here, pulled over in a parking lot writing this review with hot coffee ALL OVER ME and my car because just picking the cup up made the coffee burst up from the cup, popping up the lid. I STILL haven't even gotten a chance to taste my coffee! If I had the time I would've gone back to complain in person. The sad part is that if the service had been better, friendlier, maybe I wouldn't be as upset, but her rudeness almost made me feel as if this was almost on purpose....as a person of color, I would hate to think this was the reason for a 4.9 reviewed coffee house to deliver such poor service...
reviews_data.owner_answer: I am so sorry you had a bad experience today. I’m out of town for a wedding but I will be back next week and I’d love to make it up to you sometime.

reviews_data.review_text: Great coffee with fast and polite service. Really not much more you could ask for. Oddly enough, they've got a great beer selection at well.

reviews_data.review_text:
I don't think you could honestly get anymore of a cozy homey feeling in a cafe that your going to be getting here. Forest Trail is a house that was converted into a cafe, and it just has the most laid back and relaxing atmosphere. I had actually stopped in here a week ago with a friend and ordered a hot chai with their zucchini bread. It was so good that I had to come back again today and get the exact same thing! Their zucchini bread is so moist and delicious that I was thinking about it after I left the first time. The hot chai was also pretty good. It was a little sweet today but it still hit the spot on a rainy day.

They have anything from jazz to alternative music on their record player which really completes the atmosphere and allows you to settle in. There are also various rooms and spots where you can enjoy your coffee and baked goods. The spacious parking lot in the back is a huge plus too. This is an all around great place to grab a coffee and chill, and I will happily continue supporting this business!

reviews_data.review_text:
This coffee shop is such a hidden gem, people working there are lovely and so is their coffee and pastries. I enjoy trying all their new monthly flavors and its a great place to work/study.
I do wish they sold more savory options like sandwiches or wraps (but I believe its something planned for the future).
The only other thing is if you plan on working in the evening, check their calendar because they do have events and it can get very loud and I had to leave early due to noise and lack of space on few occasions.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Thank you so much Vicki! We do have a lot of events, that is true. Usually, Thursday, and Saturdays, and trivia Fridays happens outside now that it's warm again (if you're reading this in January of 2026 just know I'm writing it in Spring.)

We are working on our food trailer as I type this. Honestly, I'm typing this to avoid that work. No, I'm kidding but we are hoping to have savory food, cooked right here, within the coming weeks. And as for wraps and sandwiches I literally just bought some so we are adding "grab and go" (or "grab and sit and hang out and work or read") options as of this afternoon. We're excited about that. 

Best practice is to check our instagram: @foresttrailhouse to see if we have anything going on that evening or what our specials are and just to keep up to date. Thanks so much for this lovely review. We'll see you at the shop soon!

reviews_data.review_text: I wanna like this place everytime I go, but unfortunately leave disappointed. Their food is very mediocre, and the coffee is too. Their lattes never taste like what they say they are, and usually taste like they have no syrup at all. I think their aesthetic is perfect, but seems like that’s what their main focus is on, instead of good drinks & good food.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Sorry you feel this way Austin. We are always happy to add more syrup if that's what you'd like. I will defend that our drinks and food take up 90% of our bandwidth and the aesthetic is a distant third. Our espresso was selected over weeks of trail and error, it's a single origin from the Huehuetenaga region Guatemala. We do feel like the syrup should be the cherry on top of the sundae and not the sundae itself. We want you to taste the espresso and milk more than the syrup, otherwise, it becomes too sweet for us but that's just us and everyone has their own desires and ultimately we're there to please so just ask for extra syrup and we'll gladly give that to you. Our house blend for our is also a Guatemalan blend that we chose because most people like a medium dark blend. But if you really want a nice light blend you should try our pour over! It's amazing. We make all of our food in house with trained bakers. I don't know what you ordered but I'm sorry it wasn't to your liking. We know we can't win 'em all but as a small business it always hurts to get reviews like this. We take it personally and try to learn from it.

reviews_data.review_text:
This used to be our favorite coffe place because they have a wall of pictures of dogs in the shop and we found them to be very dog friendly to well behaved dogs such as ours. This put Forest Trail above other local coffee shops especially in the winter.
Today we were informed their policy has changed and we were asked to leave with our pup. There was no other customers in the store but we respected their decision and left. For us Forest Hill has lost the one attraction that set them apart from the other coffee shops so it's a matter of if their coffee is good enough to sit outside in the cold. You can probably get the same combination of syrups at McDonalds, Starbucks or Brakemans. Forest Trail should probably take down all the pictures of cute dogs in their shop.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Sorry about that Jon, it’s not our favorite rule either. You can go to ncleg.gov and see who you can write about changing it but our hands are tied. The pics will stay though, sorry. We love our outdoor pups. Also, we certainly aim to be much better than those other places and we’ll continue to push our drinks to new and better places. Anyway, sorry you were upset today. It’s been our policy since day one because it’s the law. So is it a policy? IDK, honestly, it’s just the law.

reviews_data.owner_answer:
Piper, I really am truly so sorry you had a bad experience. We strive to be better than this and I take it very personally whenever a customer has a bad experience. I understand why you won't be coming back.

For people who aren't Piper who are reading this, the way to handle this is to come to us and say you aren't happy. She ordered two fresh squeezed lemonades, which we can easily adjust to your liking, making them sweeter or more tart, however you like it. We squeeze them fresh so we can definitely help you with that! She also ordered our cold brew with a cold foam and a latte - again, these are all adjustable and if somethings wrong, please come to us. We will fix it for you.

If you're at a small business and the bathroom is dirty believe me, we're more embarrassed than you are. But there are also customers who do not care and make a mess. Please tell us. Please. Sometimes we'll got hours without being able to get into the bathrooms because we're so busy, but if you tell us, or other small businesses, we'll get in there and fix the problem. 

Small businesses rely on your input because we cannot be everywhere at all times. So tell us in the moment if you can. That way we can help. If you wait and do it on the internet, it's impossible for it to fix it for YOU.

reviews_data.review_text: I had high hopes for Forest Trail when they took over, but man am I disappointed. We just want high quality coffee in Mint Hill but they are trying to do too much rather than focusing on their main product - COFFEE! I really want to support local businesses but I would rather drive 20 minutes to another coffee shop than go to Forest Trail.
reviews_data.owner_answer: We're sorry that you don't enjoy our coffee, we understand that all tastes are different and we strive to make our customers happy. I understand that you believe we don't focus on our coffee but just for the record, you had a pumpkin spiced cold brew with oat milk vanilla cold foam. We steep that cold brew for 19 hours, we honed that pumpkin spice recipe over several days until finalizing it, an that takes us several hours to make, and the cold foam we make on the spot fresh, not from a premixed bag. After you didn't like that we happily made you a pumpkin spiced latte to replace that. Now, I'm not sure what you did not like about that but we've tasted at least 10 different espresso blends to come up with a solid medium-dark roast that will stand up to the syrups and milk that everyone adds. We want the espresso to still shine, and we think that it does. Clearly you disagree but such is life. If you do decide to try us again, you should try the actual coffee. It's great!

reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much Angelica!! This feels so great on a day when a tropical storm has us hiding while our power flickers on and off all day. Hope to see you soon!

reviews_data.review_text: Stopped by to get some coffee and treat for my wife. Coffee is tasty and hot but to my disappointment they only had full whipping cream and half and half,  no other healthier alternatives. Ordered two cinnamon rolls and they offered to heat them but I took them as is. Got to the car and mine was dry and hard, like it was old. Tried heating the second one when I got home and bleh, day old rolls. Kind  of an expensive $20 lesson for me but the coffee was good.
reviews_data.owner_answer: I'm sorry to hear that the cinnamon rolls weren't your favorites. For future reference we will always tell you when everything was baked, I know that those rolls were baked 8 hours before you came in, I went and checked in the system. We also have oat milk, unsweetened Almond milk, whole milk, and skim milk in case you decide to give us another try, which we hope you do!

reviews_data.review_text: Always love coming here, staff is great and the coffee is delicious! Great meeting spot to catch up with friends or talking business.

reviews_data.review_text: Excellent service, great coffees, I love this place!

reviews_data.review_text: We continued our quest of trying out the local coffee shops in the greater Charlotte area and ended up here.  We ordered food, coffee, and tea.  The coffee was a light/medium roast and was quite good but not our personal favorite.  The tea was excellent.  We ordered the quiche and a stinger.  The quiche was amazing but the stinger was super dry, did not contain much meat, and was difficult to eat.  We would not get the stinger again but we would eat the quiche all day long.  The location is great and there is plenty of parking out back.  The atmosphere here was really great.  We will definitely be back if only for the quiche and to try a different type of coffee.  Nice place to chill out if you are in the Mint Hill area!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Oh man, that's a bummer about the stinger! We love our stingers and it's a bummer that we missed on that one. We make everything in house and take a lot of pride in our work, we're really sorry we didn't nail it for you. Next time you should try our pour over or ask for one of our roasts in a french press, I love Cairn coffee and that's why we work with them. We've found that most of our customers love a slightly darker roast but we have lighter roasts available by the cup as well. It'll just take us a few extra minutes. Anyway, we appreciate you giving us a try! Good luck in your continued quest.

What I mean by this is that they actually are doing their job. In my judgment, they actually enjoying their job perhaps because of atmosphere. reviews_data.review_text: Okay so....today was my first time trying this coffee shop. My husband and I were out running errands and I needed a pick me up so instead trying to find a Starbucks we wanted to try local instead, which is what we prefer. Upon entering, the atmosphere is very chill and quaint, but the service was extremely lacking. When we got to the counter we were met with a rude, blank stare just waiting for our order with no hello or welcome, and then a "what are you having". I told the girl it was our first time there and we didn't see the coffee menu (to explain our delay in ordering) and she just stood there with no reply, no beckoning to where the menu was, nor a recommendation. We eventually looked around and found the menu and ordered 2 Americanos (we would've ordered more with suggestion or even friendliness but decided against it). After getting our EXTREMELY HOT coffees, we tried adding sugar to them but it melted the straws and couldn't stir. After getting into the car, the coffees were too hot to drink and started to warp the lids and coffee cups. Now I'm sitting here, pulled over in a parking lot writing this review with hot coffee ALL OVER ME and my car because just picking the cup up made the coffee burst up from the cup, popping up the lid. I STILL haven't even gotten a chance to taste my coffee! If I had the time I would've gone back to complain in person. The sad part is that if the service had been better, friendlier, maybe I wouldn't be as upset, but her rudeness almost made me feel as if this was almost on purpose....as a person of color, I would hate to think this was the reason for a 4.9 reviewed coffee house to deliver such poor service...
reviews_data.owner_answer: I am so sorry you had a bad experience today. I’m out of town for a wedding but I will be back next week and I’d love to make it up to you sometime.
